## Claude Code subagents (parallel toolset)

`.claude/agents/*.md` — 10 Claude Code subagents covering migration batching,
new-screen design, design-domain audits, minimal-diff review, architecture-debt
sweep, button/data-flow wiring audit, test writing/coverage, and PR gating
(see AGENTS.md § Claude Code Subagents). Cursor cannot invoke these directly —
different runtime — but each file is a readable runbook; open and follow it
manually for a matching task. If the user has Claude Code available, prefer
suggesting the matching subagent over re-deriving the same procedure here.
`flutter-architecture-sweep` is the Claude Code-native counterpart to
`ponytail-audit` above (uses `tokensave` instead of GitNexus, same ledger
format/location). `flutter-button-wiring-auditor` covers a gap neither
`route_coverage_audit` nor `navigation_edge_audit` catches: non-navigation
`onPressed`/`onTap` handlers that are wired to nothing.

## Optional QA (gstack)

Install once: `.\scripts\Setup-GStackBrowse.ps1` (global `~/.cursor/skills/gstack-*/`).

| Skill | When |
| --- | --- |
| `/browse` | Visual QA after UI batch — run `flutter run -d chrome` first |
| `/review` | Pre-merge supplement to `code-review-and-quality` |

**Token rule:** use gstack in a **separate QA chat**, not migration batches.

Do **not** invoke gstack plan/design skills (`plan-ceo-review`, `design-shotgun`) —
they conflict with VitTrade execution prompts.
